news.title: DVAC probes alleged PMAY fund misuse in Trichy’s Marudhur village
news.para: Inspector G Sakthivel filed a case on April 12 against 10 officials of the panchayat raj and rural development department.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body cracks whip on illegal constructions
news.para: An illegal under construction colony on Jassian road and an encroachment on road portion in Tagore Nagar were also demolished.

news.title: NCLT admits Indiabulls Housing's insolvency plea against Subhash Chandra
news.para: ​A two-member Delhi bench of the NCLT directed initiation of personal insolvency proceedings against Zee Entertainment Enterprises Ltd (ZEEL) Chairman Emeritus Chandra, who was a guarantor for a loan given to Essel group firm Vivek Infracon Ltd.

news.title: K Raheja Corp to redevelop SOBO Central Mall into luxury residences
news.para: Spread over 1.3 acres in prime Haji Ali locality, the mall is expected to make way for an around 50-storey sea-view superstructure with nearly 250,000 sq ft development potential.

news.title: Accacia raises $6.5 million in pre-series A round led by Illuminate Financial
news.para: "We have already deployed our solution to over 25 million sq ft of real estate," said Annu Talreja, founder and CEO of Accacia.

news.title: US-based Quanex to buy UK's Tyman for $976 million
news.para: The acquisition comes at a time U.S. housebuilders are cutting prices and offering other incentives to increase sales amid hurdles created for many first time buyers by higher mortgage rates.

news.title: WeWork Inc to sell 27% stake held in India unit via Rs 1,200 crore secondary deal: Sources
news.para: Enam group’s family office, A91 Partners, CaratLane’s Mithun Sacheti have acquired secondary shares in WeWork India through the transaction, said people in the know of the matter.

news.title: Kesoram Industries' net loss widens to Rs 244.42 crore in Q4 FY24
news.para: Kesoram Industries' total consolidated income stood at Rs 1,093.96 crore in Q4 FY24, a growth of from Rs 1,070.82 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Asking prices for homes in UK rise by 1.7% in April: Rightmove
news.para: Property website Rightmove said on Monday its asking prices for residential properties rose by 1.7% in the four weeks to April 13 when compared with the same period last year.

news.title: MahaRERA raises concerns over 212 housing projects launched after Jan 2023
news.para: MahaRERA expressed grave concerns over 212 housing projects launched between January and April 2023 across Maharashtra for failing to provide construction updates, breaching regulations.

news.title: Century Real Estate raises Rs 450 crore from Edelweiss to fund projects in Bengaluru
news.para: The infusion of Rs 450 crore will primarily be allocated towards the development of a new luxury project in the heart of Bengaluru. A part of the funds will also be used towards Century Trails and Century Wintersun Phase II.

news.title: Sanghi Industries to raise upto Rs 2,200 crore
news.para: The RPS shall carry a preferential right vis-à-vis equity shares of Sanghi Industries, with respect to the payment of dividend and repayment in case of winding up or repayment of capital.

news.title: New real estate projects decline in Gujarat in FY24
news.para: Gujarat's real estate market witnessed a slowdown in new project launches during FY 2023-24, attributed to factors like rising construction costs, incomplete projects, online shopping impact, and investors shifting to stocks.

news.title: Royal India Corporation invests Rs 450 crore on a residential project in Kalyan
news.para: Royal India Corporation has invested Rs 450 crore in the project spread across 2.2 acre plot. It has development potential of five lakh sq ft.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC quashes FIR filed against Emaar India
news.para: The High Court of Punjab and Haryana quashed the FIR against Emaar India and JLL India, citing undervaluation and fraud allegations as baseless. The case involved accusations of asset manipulation during demerger, with no criminal elements found in the complaint.

news.title: Shops to rentals, business blooms in Jewar as many move in from other places
news.para: Jewar's economy booms with the new airport, driving land deals and rentals. Local entrepreneurs like Virendra Kumar and Himanchal Sharma seize business opportunities.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers acquires about 1,073 sq meters land in Mumbai for Rs 33.10 crore
news.para: Rahul Rajan Jesu Thomas, whole time director of Suraj Estate Developers said, "The acquisition enhances our sales potential by Rs 120 crores, strengthening both the company's project pipeline and its financial outlook."

news.title: Companies now investing in premium office fit-outs
news.para: Savills India data reflects a shift towards premium spaces, while tech players like Tushar Mittal drive demand amidst a growing construction industry.

news.title: Lavasa creditors invoke Darwin Platform Infrastructure's guarantee
news.para: Creditors invoked a guarantee due to CIRP non-compliance, halting the Lavasa project. Legal battles continue as lenders lose confidence in the resolution applicant. NCLT and NCLAT petitions are pending, with DPIL seeking more time.

news.title: Amitabh Bachchan buys land parcel from HoABL to build luxury villa in Alibaug
news.para: Amitabh Bachchan acquires land in Alibaug for a luxury villa. Bollywood celebrities like Suhana Khan and cricketers such as Virat Kohli invest in the booming real estate market of Alibaug near Mumbai.
